contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} {{otherships|ships named Nautilus}} '''USS ''Nautilus''''' may refer to: * [[USS Nautilus (1799)|USS ''Nautilus'' (1799)]], a 12-gun schooner (1799–1812) * [[USS Nautilus (1838)|USS ''Nautilus'' (1838)]], a 76-foot coast survey schooner (1838–1859) * [[USS Nautilus (SS-168)|USS ''Nautilus'' (SS-168)]], a ''Narwhal''-class submarine (1930–1945) * [[USS Nautilus (SSN-571)|USS ''Nautilus'' (SSN-571)]], the first nuclear submarine (1954–1980) ;See also *[[USS H-2 (SS-29)|USS ''H-2'' (SS-29)]], a ''H''-class submarine (1913–1930) called ''Nautilus'' only during construction *[[USS Nautilus II (SP-559)|USS ''Nautilus II'' (SP-559)]], a 66-foot patrol/escort (1917–1919) *[[USS O-12 (SS-73)|USS ''O-12'' (SS-73)]], an ''O-11''-class submarine (1917–1931) which carried the name ''Nautilus'' during a civilian arctic expedition in 1931 {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Nautilus, Uss}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
